ri left the garden she realized one thing, she was ready to face the world.  She knew that her powers were still developing and she would need to practice them to move up.  There were places in her talent that lay latent and only time and use would unearth them.  But no longer could she remain sheltered here.<br>
<br>
She had trained with weapons and fists, her instruments were as nice as the temple could afford.  And was given knowledge of what she would be able to do in time, now she just needed to move forward and do it.  The hardest test had been passed this very eve in the eyes of the Lady, but her heart was heavy.  <br>
<br>
Up to her room she went, and opened her dresser.  Under her small clothes she found the note.  Picking it up. she read the only words that linked her to her parents.   Walking to the window she laid it against her chest, “You are out there Daddy.  I wonder what you are like?“ Sitting down in the chair and looking out, “You don’t even know I am here needing to know you.  I wonder what is sadder, not knowing what is missing in your life, or knowing you are missing something and not being able to reach it?”<br>
<br>
Crossing back over to the dresser she begins to pack.  “First I will go and join the bard guild in Freeport, then I will see the lands of this world.”  She packed everything in the room that was hers and got out pen and parchment.  <br>
<br>
Kes had never said goodbye to anyone before and was not sure how to do it.  She would thank the people that helped her by penning each of them a heart filled note.  Thinking that Arean’s would be the hardest she decided to wait on his, but when she got to Brenton’s she could not write as the tears blurred the ink.  Laying her head on the desk and crying softly she started to doubt her decision to leave.<br>
<br>
Someone knocked softly on her door composing herself she opened it.  Brenton stood there with a serious look on his face.  He surveyed the room and saw her bags, “Good, I see you know what time it is. You are a woman grown of 16 years and a talent the likes I have never seen.  This world shudders in anticipation of your adventures.”  She ran into his arms then, crying softly.  “Don’t cry Kes, you and I both know you need to go.  I have taught you all I can and now you must gain experience and learn what this world offers you.”<br>
<br>
He hugged her tight, her platinum blonde head only coming to the middle of his chest.  In her was the power to become a great bard, and there were so few out there.  “You are a shining star Kes, don’t ever forget that.”  He stepped back from her and handed her something from his pocket.  Leaning forward he kissed her cheek then turned and left.  <br>
<br>
She opened her hand and inside it gleamed a lambent stone, one of the mystical gems needed to perform a quest to gain her special favors and armor.  Closing her hand again she moved to her bags and tucked it away.  She moved the bags from the bed and lay down on the bed.  Tomorrow she would start her journey and so tonight she will rest.<br>
